reviewText: RVD VS Randy Orton in a Stretcher match: RVD sold his injury very well but this match was slow and boring. The ending was a surprise and the aftermath was brutal.Tommy Dreamer, Sandman, CM Punk VS Elijah Burke, Matt Striker and Marcus Cor Von: A very short match that could have been give more time. I miss Sandman.Hardys VS World's Greatest Tag Team in a ladder match: This might be the worst ladder match in the history of the WWE. Many moves were botched and both teams didnt look like they wanted to be hit by a ladder. Hardys retain in the worst ladder match i've ever witnessed.Kane VS Mark Henry: Ugh. The lumberjacks on the outside have more talent then the two in the ring. 2 lumberjacks attack Kane and help Henry win via bearhug. What's this the 60's?Vince McMahon VS Bobby Lashley: I refuse to watch this match. McMahon may have brought back ECW but in the early days he basically butchered the company and made the ECW originals his whipping boys. McMahon had such a big ego that he won the ECW title, which was the day ECW died. Lashley was a dime a dozen strong man, who i've always hated. He cannot wrestle and he cannot talk, kind of like a mix between Ahmed Johnson and Ultimate Warrior. Again, a more talented wrestler on the outside looking in-Umaga.Maria and Santina do a back stage promo. Maria does her famous i'm a ditz but smart when asked a question. Then she kisses Candice Michelle for good luck. I use to like Maria before WWE whored her up.Pudding Match-Skip, go watch lesbian porn instead.Edge VS Batista in a Cage match: A very good cage match with the classic two men hit the ground first but whose is the winner? ending.Khali VS Cena in a Falls Count Anywhere match: Two men with limited wrestling talent but I have enjoyed Cena in hardcore matches. The main event is kept short-about 15 minutes-for a reason. Khali dominates the match but Cena pulls out the FU out of nowhere and wins. What the f&*(?A very bad event as WWE was in a funk at the time. The cage match was the only good thing about the event and Maria kissing anther woman was cool. Do not buy this event unless you got to have every WWE dvd.

reviewText: Unlike the previous two years where this was an ECW event, all of WWE was represented on this PPV and after seeing the last ECW PPV...count your blessings that this wasn't an Vince McMahon ECW show.  The format is very similar to how WCW did their Uncensored PPV back in '95 & how WWE does their Taboo Tuesday/Cyber Sunday events in which every match has a special stipulation/gimmick to it.  It made for a very unique PPV by WWE standards.Stretcher Match: RVD vs. Randy Orton - The rules for this one are to put your opposition on a stretcher & carry them across the finish line at the entrance way.  As a personal note, this is ironic for me since this is RVD's last match in WWE & one of the very first RVD matches I ever saw was against Sabu in ECW...in a stretcher match.  This match had RVD selling his concussion from the previous week while Orton was targeting his head.  RVD was able to pull off the shocking upset win in the end but Orton got the last word with him delivering a DDT onto the floor with RVD hanging off the barricade.Tables Match: Tommy Dreamer, Sandman, C.M. Punk vs. New Breed - ECW comes back to the event that they created.  This match was real short & was the usual ECW style brawl similar to their WM match with it not having enough time for everyone to get their spots in but it was a good entertaining match for what it was.Ladder Match: World Tag Team Champions The Hardys vs. World's Greatest Tag Team - Knowing the Hardys reputation in ladder matches with this being Jeff's 4th ladder match & Matt's 3rd in under a year along with Shelton's showstealing performances in the first two Money In The Bank along with him & Hass' outstanding performance in their "forgotten" ladder match again Tajiri & Eddie Guerrero...you just knew this was going to be the match of the night which it was.  The match started out as a brawl then the ladders were brought into play to make moves more high impact such as Hass being slammed off the top rope onto the ladder, Shelton being backdropped on one lying on the ring apron, and the Hardys shoving Hass & Benjamin off the ladder with Shelton going over the top rope & hitting a ladder on the way down.  This wasn't a spotfest but was still a great match that was worthy of going on the ladder match DVD if this match happened earlier in the year.Lumberjack Match: Kane vs. Mark Henry - Eventhough it was a lumberjack, Kane & Henry made it clear that they didn't need or want any help to get back into the ring whenever they were knocked out.  This was the typical lumberjack match where the heels will help the heel as the faces did the same for the face.  In the ring, this was a nice for a big man match with Henry not having to be carried or Kane overselling Henry's offense to make him look credible.  The ending with Kane passing out in a bearhug was the only weak point in this match for me.Street Fight Match: ECW Champion Mr. McMahon vs. Bobby Lashley - As expected, Shane McMahon & Umaga came out with Mr. McMahon and look out for Lashley doing a "crash & burn" trying to dive over the top onto Umaga. The match for the most part was just like their previous match at Backlash where Shane & Umaga did the dirty work with Mr. McMahon getting in his cheap shots with Lashley only getting his offense in when they made a mistake towards the end of the match.  This was the most watchable match out of their series & served it's purpose of Lashley defying the odds & getting back his ECW title but besides that, nothing special here.Pudding Match: Candice Michelle vs. Melina - With the expection of Candice almost losing her top & Melina's bikini, this was wrestlecrap at it's best.Steel Cage Match: World Champion Edge vs. Batista - Well, this heavily makes up for their Judgment Day match as Batista did carry his own weight here in this cage match.  It's wasn't a bloody massacre but a watchable matchup.Falls Count Anywhere Match: WWE Champion John Cena vs. Great Khali - This was just like Judgment Day in the fact that Cena had to oversell Khali's offense to make the match someone watchable with the difference this time being that he actually got some  more (but not much) offense in & used weapons like the camera boom to help him out.  But in a nutshell, it was a clone of their Judgment Day match...a victory for Cena over the "monster" Khali.DVD extras include a post match interviews with Cena, Henry, and Edge along with the RVD/Orton match from the previous RAW.Overall, the first three matches were the best ones while the cage match was watchable.  The rest of the matches were passable & nothing really memorable or anything to hurry up & rush to see but it looks better in comparison to the lackluster Judgment Day.  I recommend this for a rental & make up your own mind.

reviewText: One Night Stand 2007When I bought this DVD the first thing I said to myself after it was done was "UGH". Seriously, I hadn't been this disappointed with a WWE PPV since No Way Out 2002. I just felt that there was way too much controversy surrounding this PPV and it added up to a lackluster show that ends with a little bit of a smack to the face. For me, One Night Stand was supposed to be one of 2 ECW events of the year and after the poor December 2 Dismember a few months prior, things could only go up from there. I never knew I could be more wrong.So I mentioned there were controversies surrounding this PPV and here they are. Controversy #1, Rob Van Dam's last match in WWE... with Randy Orton???? OK, so I get it "The Legend Killer" and what not but I'll go there, Randy Orton does not impress me as a wrestler. The guy's technical skills are adequate at best and you'd think with the style mismatch we'd at least get a little entertainment. Not to mention this match is a Stretcher Match! When I think of RVD and Stretcher Matches, I think RVD v Sabu. A highly physical match up that goes above and beyond the limits of imagination. This Stretcher Match doesn't even come close. Terry Funk was once quoted as saying, "The best way to go out, is on your back". If that was the case, RVD went out upside down because it's such an awkward feeling watching that because for those of us who've seen RVD really go full throttle we know that the man can get it done and to watch him go out like this almost feels insulting.Speaking of insults, Controversy #2... Vince McMahon defends the ECW World Heavyweight Championship against Bobby Lashley (w/ the helpf of Shane McMahon and Umaga). First and foremost, WHAT THE HELL? Vinny Mac the ECW Champ? OK so I will admit that Vince has taken some brutal beatings from Austin, HHH, Undertaker and others but is Vince "hardcore"? Survey says..... NO! If you ask me this match is no better than an over-hyped squash. Not to mention with Lashley's amateur background you'd think he'd be an amazing chain wrestler but NO. He ends up being your "A" typical strong man wrestler. So not only do we have a squash we, have BOREDOM. Wonderful (sorry, sarcasm doesn't come across as funny when it's written).I will say that even with those 2 major problems, there are flashes of  brilliance in the 6-Man Tables Match between the team of Tommy Dreamer, Sandman and CM Punk v Elijah Burke, Matt Striker and Marcus Cor Van (ugh, seriously why can't we just call him Monty Brown?). Sure this match wasn't nearly as crazy as other Tables matches but for what it was, it was entertaining. Personally if this match had been an Elimination Tables Match it probably would've gotten over more but again, take it as it is.The other shot of brilliance was the Tornado Tag Ladder Match between The Hardys and Shelton Benjamin and Charlie Haas. I've always been a fan of Shelton's (go Gophers!) and the guy can put on a show when it comes to Ladder matches. I just love watching these 4 take the risks that they do in this match. Sure Charlie Haas doesn't take the same kind of risks that Matt, Jeff and Shelton do but the guy can take some punishment. If you ask me, this was probably the best match of the night. Then again, there was that Extreme Lumberjack Match between Kane and Mark Henry (again, more sarcasm).So overall, this PPV to me is a 1  star PPV (but closer to 1). PASS. No question about it, PASS. I'd like to say that there are some redeeming factors to One Night Stand 07 but there's really not. To only have 2 somewhat entertaining matches on card is plain out pathetic. That's like end of the line WCW like. I really hate to dog this PPV so bad but I don't want anyone else to have the same disappointment I had when I watched this PPV.

reviewText: WWE One Night Stand. It's absolutely nothing like the two One Night Stand shows before it, as those were ECW shows. This is a WWE show, so don't expect the same action you got from the previous One Night Stands. It has some matches worth checking out particularly early on, but it also has a few craptastic stinkers as the card goes on.1. Stretcher Match- Rob Van Dam vs. Randy Orton= This is a true blue storytelling match. And for the most part, it tells it well. However, there are a few spots in here that really make you feel like if they had let these two just go at it without the concussion angle, they really could've torn in up. But still, not bad. 3 out of 5.2. Six Man Tag Team Tables Match- CM Punk, The Sandman and Tommy Dreamer vs. Elijah Burke, Marcus Cor Von and Matt Striker= Fun match. Not too long, but moves at a nice pace. Won't be anything mind-blowing, but it's just an entertaining tables match. 3 out of 5.3. Ladder Match- The Hardys vs. The World's Greatest Tag Team(World Tag Team Championship)= There are some ladder matches that are considered all time classics. Then are some ladder matches, for whatever reason, go completely unnoticed. This is one of the unnoticed ladder matches. You have a conversation about some of the best ladder matches in history, this one will rarely come up. But it should. You have two of the greatest tag teams in history going at it in a ladder match. Great action, great spots, this is one to watch. 5 out of 5.4. Lumberjack Match- Kane vs. Mark Henry= Wow, Chris Benoit as a lumberjack for this abomination, what a great way to spend your last PPV. Slow, plodding and boring, this match isn't worth the time or frustration. Skip this one. 1 out of 5.5. Street Fight- Vince McMahon vs. Bobby Lashley(ECW Championship)= Pretty decent match. Features the usual Shane O' Mac highspots, so you should know what to expect there. Nothing terrible, moderately enjoyable, but nothing you'll really wanna see again after it's done. 2 out of 5.6. Pudding Match- Melina vs. Candice Michelle= The worst "match" I've ever seen. And I've seen alot of bad matches. No redeeming qualities, I don't even see how anybody can find this sexy like they would a Bra and Panties match, it looks like they were smeared in diarrhea. Just do yourself a favor and skip. 1 out of 5.7. Steel Cage Match- Edge vs. Batista(World Heavyweight Championship)= This match hit the ground walking, and it never picked up steam. You never had a sense of excitement in this one, it was essentially a borefest. It wasn't as bad as the other 1 out of 5's on this list, but still, this isn't something worth looking forward to. 1 out of 5.8. Falls Count Anywhere- John Cena vs. The Great Khali(WWE Championship)= The Great Khali should never be in a main event, ever. Cena tried, he really did, and hell, he managed to carry Khali to one of the better matches of his sorry career. But it's still terrible. I can't believe this ever main evented one PPV, let alone two. 1 out of 5.I never thought I'd give a PPV that featured a 5 out of 5 rated match only 1 star, but that's when happens when you put on crap awful main events. It's cheap enough where I can recommend a purchase for the Ladder match alone, so you won't be out too much for this one. But still, don't expect much of anything out of any match after it.

reviewText: 80-76%-perfect75-71%-awsome70-66%-good65-61%-poor60-56%-awful1. RVD vs. Randy Orton in a stretcher match- This match was pretty good. This most likely was RVD's last match and it was a good one. They came into this match playing up the fact that RVD had a concussion and it played out in the match pretty well. There were a couple of botched spots in this match but RVD also had some good ones when he did a flying move over the tope rope and missed Orton but nailed the stretcher. RVD got the surprise win but after the match Orton laid him out. Winner RVD. Match Rating 7/10.2. The New Breed vs. The Originals in a tables match- This was another solid match. Just a lot of fast paced action in it. It was only about 7 minutes long but there was non stop action. There is not a whole lot to say about this match except there were a couple of nice spots. Winner The New Breed. Match Rating 6.5/10.3. The Hardy Boyz vs. The Worlds Greatest Tag Team in a ladder match for the World Tag Team Titles- This match went really good. This was the match that in my opinion saved this ppv. For a first timer these two teams did a great job. This match was also just non stop action and spot fest galore. There was a couple moves were Matt hardy through Shelton into the ladder. Matt was set up on the outside and Shelton jumped off a ladder inside the ring onto matt. Shelton also went to hit Matt and he got back dropped over the top rope onto the ladder outside the ring. As you can see a great match and a high point on this ppv. Winner and still World Tag Team Champs the Hardy Boyz. Match Rating 8.5/10.4. Mark Henry vs. Kane Lumberjack- This was when the match started to sink quite a bit. Now I was not expecting this match to be good and I was right it sucked. Henry is so old now he can barley move and Kane tired to carry him to a good match it did just not work. Not much to say about this match except you can skip it. Winner Mark Henry. Match Rating 2.5/10.5. Vince McMahon vs. Bobby Lashley in a street fight- This match was not as bad as there last match at judgment day that lasted less than 2 minutes. This was a three on one match to start anyway but lashley ended taking Umaga and Shane down to leave this up to Vince and him and he took advantage. There were some nice spots in this match including a couple of chair shots to the head of Vince and the back of Lashley. Shane went for a dropkick into a trash can into Bobby's face but missed and Lashley took Vince out with the spear to win the title from Vince. Winner and new ECW champ Bobby Lashley. Match Rating 5.5/10.6. Candice Michelle vs. Melina in a pudding match- This was about the time were you can get ready to sleep. This match all around just sucked. The girls were hot as hell but besides that it was horrible. I think the only move they pulled off was throwing pudding at each other why the hell is this match on a ppv card. Skip this except the beginning. Winner Candice Michelle. Match Rating 2/10.7. Edge vs. Batista for the World Heavyweight Title in a steel match- This was another high spot on the ppv. These two had a match at judgement and it was not that good. They started out a little slow here but than the match picked up. There were several times in this match were there were a lot of close calls to escaping the cage but every time it did not happen. There were a lot of near falls off the moves in the ring including batista kicking out of a spear. The match ended were Edge won cleanly again which was a surprise. Good job by both men. Winner and still WHC Edge. Match Rating 8/10.8. John Cena vs. The Great Kalhi in a street fight for the WWE Title- This was another poor main event put on by WWE. Like last months match Kalhi dominated the whole thing till the end which was really boring. This was about a 10 minute match which is awful for the main event and for him to get dominated the whole match and pull it out was ridiculous. Another bad thing is he wins every time and that's not winning viewers it losing them. Winner and still WWE champ John Cena. Match Rating 4.5/10.Well that raps up another. I would give ECW One Night Stand 2007 a grade of 44.5/80 which is a 56% which means this is an awful ppv. It sounds bad but there were not a lot of matches that were good except for the tag team ladder match. If you can tell me if my review was helpful or not I would appreciate that. Thanks for your time.
summary: ECW ONE NIGHT STAND 2007 IS A 1 STAR PPV
